      <hedline>
        <hl1>Let Fresh Kills Be</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nigel Rollings letter comments on August 13 article on plans for Fresh Kills landfill on Staten Island when it closes in January 2001 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor</p>
        <p>Re ''Fresh Kills, Chapter 2'' (news article, Aug. 13):</p>
        <p>The comments and suggestions of people who were asked what should be done with the Fresh Kills landfill when it closes in January were clever and humorous, except for the proposal by Guy V. Molinari, the Staten Island borough president, to build another highway,</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor</p>
        <p>Re ''Fresh Kills, Chapter 2'' (news article, Aug. 13):</p>
        <p>The comments and suggestions of people who were asked what should be done with the Fresh Kills landfill when it closes in January were clever and humorous, except for the proposal by Guy V. Molinari, the Staten Island borough president, to build another highway,</p>
        <p>I would like to make my own proposal. Do nothing. Why not enjoy the simple contours of these man-made hills for their intrinsic value -- visually clear, uncluttered open space that might be welcomed by many residents and the wildlife of Staten Island?</p>
        <p>NIGEL ROLLINGS  Long Island City, Queens  Aug. 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
